   "id": "7b58f36f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "title: \"Deep Dive — How Step 5 Works and Why It Succeeds\"\n",
    "format:\n",
    "  html:\n",
    "    toc: true\n",
    "    toc-depth: 3\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "b29b37d3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#| echo: false\n",
    "#| warning: false\n",
    "import polars as pl, re\n",
    "import plotly.graph_objects as go\n",
    "import plotly.express as px\n",
    "\n",
    "CSV = '/Users/omkarmalpure/Documents/broadjump_v2/analyze-data/UOM-38552.csv'\n",
    "df = pl.read_csv(CSV, null_values=['', 'NULL'])\n",
    "\n",
    "step5_df     = df.filter(pl.col('RecognizedUOMMatchReason').str.starts_with('Step 5').fill_null(False))\n",
    "unrecog_df   = df.filter(pl.col('IsRecognized') == False)\n",
    "total        = len(df)\n",
    "step5_count  = len(step5_df)\n",
    "unrecog      = len(unrecog_df)\n",
    "\n",
    "def extract_score(r):\n",
    "    if not r: return None\n",
    "    m = re.search(r'Proximity Score ([\\d.]+)', r)\n",
    "    return float(m.group(1)) if m else None\n",
    "\n",
    "def extract_winner(r):\n",
    "    if not r: return 'Unknown'\n",
    "    if 'File UOM WAP' in r or ('FileUOM' in r and 'WAP' in r): return 'FileUOM WAP'\n",
    "    if 'WAP candidate' in r: return 'EA/1 WAP'\n",
    "    if 'KnownProductUOM' in r: return 'Known Product UOM'\n",
    "    if 'DBSCAN' in r: return 'DBSCAN'\n",
    "    return 'Other'\n",
    "\n",
    "reasons = step5_df['RecognizedUOMMatchReason'].to_list()\n",
    "step5_df = step5_df.with_columns([\n",
    "    pl.Series('parsed_score',  [extract_score(r)   for r in reasons]),\n",
    "    pl.Series('winner_source', [extract_winner(r)  for r in reasons]),\n",
    "])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ce15266b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 1 — DBSCAN-Built Thresholds (ThresholdV2)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why the old thresholds (V1) were not enough\n",
    "\n",
    "Steps 1–4 rely on hand-crafted or statistically naive min/max price ranges.  A single\n",
    "extreme purchase can widen a V1 threshold so much that it matches too broadly — or, when\n",
    "data is sparse, the range is too tight to match realistic new transactions.\n",
    "\n",
    "### What DBSCAN does differently\n",
    "\n",
    "**DBSCAN** (Density-Based Spatial Clustering of Applications with Noise) groups historical\n",
    "purchase prices for each product into *dense clusters* while treating statistical outliers\n",
    "as noise.  The resulting ThresholdV2 records store:\n",
    "\n",
    "- `MinThreshold` / `MaxThreshold` — the actual observed price range of the cluster (not a\n",
    "  hand-tuned rule).\n",
    "- `QuantityOfEAInUOM` — the UOM quantity that cluster represents.\n",
    "- `MeanEA` — a per-each price anchor used when no WAP entry is available.\n",
    "\n",
    "Because outliers are excluded, the clusters are tighter and more representative of real\n",
    "analyst expectations.  A product that historically sells as a **BX/12** at $120–$180 will\n",
    "produce one cluster with that range; a separate cluster covers the **EA** sales at $10–$15.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Part 2 — The Proximity Inference Formula\n",
    "\n",
    "Once DBSCAN clusters exist, Step 5 must decide which cluster (UOM) best explains the\n",
    "current line's `PriceUOM`.  The key insight is that price operates on a **log scale** —\n",
    "a $5 difference matters much more at a $10 product than at a $10,000 product.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Log-distance calculation\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "logPrice = log₁₀(max(PriceUOM, 0.0001))\n",
    "logLo    = log₁₀(max(MinThreshold, 0.0001))\n",
    "logHi    = log₁₀(max(MaxThreshold, 0.0001))\n",
    "\n",
    "logDist  = 0                        if  lo ≤ price ≤ hi\n",
    "         = logPrice − logHi         if  price > hi   (above range)\n",
    "         = logLo − logPrice         if  price < lo   (below range)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "If the price falls *inside* the cluster band, the log-distance is exactly 0 — a perfect\n",
    "match.  Outside the band the distance grows as the log ratio between the price and the\n",
    "nearest edge.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Gaussian proximity score\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "proximityScore = exp(−0.5 × (logDist / LOG_EPS)²)    where LOG_EPS = 0.25\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "This is a **Gaussian kernel on log-price space**.  `LOG_EPS = 0.25` corresponds to roughly\n",
    "a 1.8× price deviation from the cluster edge before the score drops to ~0.37.  At a 2×\n",
    "deviation the score is ~0.02 — effectively zero.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why this mirrors analyst reasoning:**\n",
    "\n",
    "Analysts verify a UOM assignment by mentally checking whether the price is \"in the right\n",
    "ballpark\" for that product and pack size.  A box of 10 syringes should cost roughly 10×\n",
    "what one syringe costs.  If the file price is 3× or 20× off, the analyst rejects it.\n",
    "The proximity score formalises this intuition: prices within the cluster score near 1.0,\n",
    "prices slightly outside drop gracefully, and wildly mismatched prices score near 0.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Four candidate pools\n",
    "\n",
    "Step 5 evaluates up to four candidate sources and picks the one with the highest proximity\n",
    "score:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Source | What it is | Why it's included |\n",
    "|--------|-----------|-------------------|\n",
    "| **DBSCAN** | Cluster from ThresholdV2 | Primary signal — density-derived from history |\n",
    "| **Known Product UOM** | WAP (Weighted Avg Price) from purchase history | Covers UOMs not yet in DBSCAN clusters |\n",
    "| **EA/1 WAP** | Per-each derived from any known WAP ÷ quantity | Catches single-unit sales missing from DBSCAN |\n",
    "| **File UOM × WAP** | File-stated UOM quantity × per-each WAP | Validates when the supplier already labelled the pack size |\n",
    "\n",
    "The File UOM candidate requires a minimum score of **0.85** to be considered — a stricter\n",
    "bar because file labels are not always reliable.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Winner-Source Breakdown"
   ]
  },
