      "expression": "f\"{100*(step5_count-dbscan_n)/step5_count:.1f}\"",
      "result": {
       "data": {
        "text/plain": "'6.4'"
       },
       "metadata": {},
       "status": "ok"
      }
     }
    ]
   },
   "source": [
    "| Candidate | Recognitions | % of Step 5 total |\n",
    "|-----------|-------------:|------------------:|\n",
    "| DBSCAN cluster | `{python} f\"{dbscan_n:,}\"` | `{python} f\"{100*dbscan_n/step5_count:.1f}\"` % |\n",
    "| Known Product UOM (WAP) | `{python} f\"{known_n:,}\"` | `{python} f\"{100*known_n/step5_count:.1f}\"` % |\n",
    "| EA/1 WAP candidate | `{python} f\"{ea1_n:,}\"` | `{python} f\"{100*ea1_n/step5_count:.1f}\"` % |\n",
    "| File UOM × WAP | `{python} f\"{file_n:,}\"` | `{python} f\"{100*file_n/step5_count:.1f}\"` % |\n",
    "\n",
    ": {.striped .hover}\n",
    "\n",
    "DBSCAN is the dominant winner (`{python} f\"{100*dbscan_n/step5_count:.1f}\"` %), validating that\n",
    "the density-based clusters are the most reliable signal.  The remaining `{python} f\"{100*(step5_count-dbscan_n)/step5_count:.1f}\"` %\n",
    "are split across the three supplementary pools — each of which catches a class of products\n",
    "the primary DBSCAN clusters do not yet cover.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Top 10 Assigned UOMs (Step 5)"
   ]
  },
