   "source": [
    "| Purchase history | Unrecognized rows | % of total unrecognized |\n",
    "|-----------------|------------------:|------------------------:|\n",
    "| Zero (no history at all) | `{python} f\"{len(no_ph):,}\"` | `{python} f\"{no_ph_pct:.1f}\"` % |\n",
    "| Very low (1–4 units) | `{python} f\"{len(low_ph):,}\"` | `{python} f\"{low_ph_pct:.1f}\"` % |\n",
    "| Some history (≥ 5 units) | `{python} f\"{len(some_ph):,}\"` | `{python} f\"{some_ph_pct:.1f}\"` % |\n",
    "\n",
    ": {.striped .hover}\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Zero history** — DBSCAN cannot form a cluster without past transactions.  No ThresholdV2\n",
    "  exists, and no WAP can be derived.  Step 5 has nothing to anchor its proximity calculation\n",
    "  against.\n",
    "- **Very low history (1–4 units)** — a single purchase creates a technically valid cluster,\n",
    "  but with such sparse data the cluster edges may be wildly unrepresentative.  The proximity\n",
    "  score lands below the 0.30 acceptance threshold.\n",
    "- **Some history but low confidence** — the product has enough data for DBSCAN, but the\n",
    "  file's `PriceUOM` is far enough from every cluster that no candidate scores ≥ 0.30.\n",
    "  This typically means the supplier is quoting an unusual pack size not yet seen in history,\n",
    "  or there is a unit-price vs pack-price mismatch in the file.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3. PriceUOM not present in purchase history\n",
    "\n",
    "Some rows have a `PriceUOM` value but that price point has never appeared in the product's\n",
    "purchase history.  With no matching cluster and no comparable WAP anchor, the inference\n",
    "step cannot form a confident assignment — the proximity score for every candidate falls\n",
    "below 0.30 and the row exits unrecognized.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "*See **Proposed Solutions** for how these three failure modes can be addressed.*"
   ]
  }
 ],
